            "text": "According to Hagerty, there’s the potential for different European nations to consider a classic car a type of “goods” at their border. That would mean requiring the driver to secure an Access/Temporary Access Carnet before driving through. The whole point is to protect against the illegal importation of goods, something criminals would definitely try doing using something easily transportable like a car.",
